description:
In main() at lines 146-154:
```c
if (gpio_is_ready_dt(&led)) {
    ret = gpio_pin_configure_dt(&led, GPIO_OUTPUT_ACTIVE);
    if (ret < 0) {
        LOG_ERR(...);
    } else {
        led_configured = true;
        led_set(1);
    }
}
```

led_configured is declared at line 37 as a static bool, so it's zero-initialized (false) by C rules.

If gpio_is_ready_dt() returns false, led_configured remains false, and led_set() becomes a no-op (correct).
If gpio_is_ready_dt() returns true but configure fails, led_configured remains false, and led_set() is a no-op (correct).
If both succeed, led_configured = true and led_set works.

NO BUG - static initialization to false is correct behavior.
